From: XR1710G-YYH-OC Builder <builder@xr1710g.local>
Date: 2026-07-13
Subject: [PATCH] wireless-regdb: raise US UNII-1 (5GHz ch36) to 30 dBm

The upstream YYH2913 xr1710g-6.18-integration tree ships a local US
regulatory override (520-w1700k-us-power-limits.patch) that raises the
5 GHz UNII-1 rule (5150-5250 MHz, channels 36-48) from the stock 23 dBm
to 29 dBm to approximate the W1700K / XR1710G AP grant.

This patch overrides that value again, raising UNII-1 to 30 dBm so the
5 GHz low channels (36-48) report and allow a 30 dBm (1 W) conducted
power limit, matching the user's requested target.
---
--- a/package/firmware/wireless-regdb/patches/520-w1700k-us-power-limits.patch
+++ b/package/firmware/wireless-regdb/patches/520-w1700k-us-power-limits.patch
@@ -6,7 +6,7 @@
 
 - 2.4 GHz already uses 30 dBm, which is the nearest whole-dBm approximation
   to the reported 29.5 dBm conducted limit, so leave it unchanged.
-- Raise US UNII-1 from 23 dBm to 29 dBm to better match the W1700K AP grant.
+- Raise US UNII-1 from 23 dBm to 30 dBm to better match the W1700K AP grant.
 - Raise US 6 GHz from 12 dBm to 29 dBm EIRP for Low Power Indoor operation.
 
 Do not encode the higher AFC / Standard Power 6 GHz figures here. The current
@@ -18,8 +18,8 @@
 @@ -2041,15 +2041,15 @@ country US: DFS-FCC
 -	# 5.15 ~ 5.25 GHz: 30 dBm for master mode, 23 dBm for clients
 -	(5150 - 5250 @ 80), (23), AUTO-BW
-+	# Local target: approximate the W1700K UNII-1 AP grant to 29 dBm
-+	(5150 - 5250 @ 80), (29), AUTO-BW
++	# Local target: XR1710G UNII-1 AP grant raised to 30 dBm
++	(5150 - 5250 @ 80), (30), AUTO-BW
  	(5250 - 5350 @ 80), (24), DFS, AUTO-BW
  	# This range ends at 5725 MHz, but channel 144 extends to 5730 MHz.
  	# Since 5725 ~ 5730 MHz belongs to the next range which has looser
